article.description: — Marcus Hammond had 19 points as Niagara edged past Youngstown State 58-53 on Sunday.
article.headline: Hammond lifts Niagara past Youngstown St. 58-53
article.linkText: Hammond lifts Niagara past Youngstown St. 58-53
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- — Marcus Hammond had 19 points as Niagara edged past Youngstown State 58-53 on Sunday. Sam Iorio had 10 points for Niagara (2-3). Rob Brown III added six rebounds. Jordan Cintron had seven rebounds. Shemar Rathan-Mayes had 12 points for the Penguins (2-3). Michael Akuchie added 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
